title: Function/eval calls violate strict CSP
body:
The webpack configurations for TS packages emit code like `g = g || Function("return this")() || (1,eval)("this");`, which cannot run in security-critical contexts with strict CSP; e.g. in Browser extensions.

This can be fixed by adding `devtool: "source-map", node: { global: false }` to the webpack configuration (see webpack/webpack#5627).

Additionally, the `@paddlejs-mediapipe/opencv` is built by emscripten to include `Function` code evaluation. Emscripten needs parameters `-s NO_DYNAMIC_EXECUTION=1` to disable use of Function/eval (see [this answer](https://stackoverflow.com/a/64814360/1598293) on stackoverflow).
